Package: SummaryStatsPkg
Title: Summary Statistics for Dataframes
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: 
    person("Anika", "Nag", email = "nag.anika1@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: summary_statistics function provides a quick and easy way to calculate and view the summary statistics of specified numeric columns of a dataset. It creates a new dataframe with columns representing the following summary statistics: mean, median, standard_deviation and count of all non-NA values. Each row represents a specified column of the original dataset.  
